CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1936, pg. A5, reads: "Champ, Manager and Celebs at East-West - Upper photo, left to right, shows Oscar DePriest, former Congressman; William Harrison, prominent Chicago business man and manager of the Grand Hotel; John Henry Lewis, light heavywieght [heavyweight] champion of the world, and Gus Greenlee, manager of the champ and owner of the Pittsburgh Crawfords, at the East-West game."
TitMainTitle: Copy of a photograph of Oscar DePriest, William Harrison, John Henry Lewis, and Gus Greenlee at East-West All Star game at Comiskey Park, Chicago, with baseball players in background
